{
  "text": "Many previous studies have shown that podocyte depletion leads to glomerulosclerosis [CITATION_1] . To calculate the number of podocytes in glomeruli, the number of WT-1 and DAPI double-positive cells was counted. We found significantly decreased number of WT-1 positive nuclei in glomeruli in the ADR group compared with the control group (control group: 17.10 ± 1.02 versus ADR group: 8.27 ± 0.46, < 0.05). In contrast, the number of nuclei was restored in mice with ADR-induced nephropathy that received gemigliptin (ADR group: 8.27 ± 0.46 versus ADR+GM group: 15.60 ± 1.12, < 0.01; Figure 5(a) ). In the ADR group, WT-1 staining intensity was reduced, but this change was inhibited in the ADR+GM group (ADR group: 8.27 ± 0.39 versus ADR+GM group: 15.60 ± 0.94, < 0.0001; Figure 5(b) ).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "205185285"
